## WHAT CHANGED IN FINAL PASS (TOP EDITS)

**Edit 1 -- Trimmed to NYT length (~800 words from ~1,480).**
The BP078 draft was correctly flagged at ~1,480 words, above NYT guest essay range. Final pass removed: the full "Economics" section block (condensed to a single tight paragraph), the detailed benchmark honest-disclosure section (L08/L09/L10 caveats), the detailed SSPL license / Pledge paragraph, the Mirror Clause full paragraph (condensed to 2 sentences inside Step 3), the Founding Three Hundred section (not in BP078 -- also not present), and the "Why this is Step X" closing lines per section (implied by structure). The six-step structure, all canonical numbers, and all load-bearing narrative claims were preserved.

**Edit 2 -- Removed Step 3 FOUNDER EXPANSION placeholder and resolved with confirmed claims only.**
The BP078 draft contained an explicit HTML comment placeholder: "Step 3 missing content per BP078 directive. Add prose covering Bounty Posters / Cold Starts / confirm-that-this-is-real bounty posters." Since Founder has not provided this content and it is not disk-backed, the final pass resolved Step 3 using only confirmed, disk-backed claims (Rally Group, Defense Klaus, KSAT documented Hood Uber, Mirror Clause). No placeholder language appears in the submission-ready version.

**Edit 3 -- Added "16 live initiatives" to the origin paragraph.**
The BP078 draft cited "36 live production systems" in the origin block. Canonical count for the outward-facing figure is 16 initiatives (per MEMORY.md initiativeCount). "36 production systems" is the technical count that belongs in the longer Substack version. The NYT version now reads "16 live initiatives" consistent with public-facing canon. The "36 production systems" figure was removed to avoid confusion and potential overclaim on a metric that needs disambiguation for a general audience.

